<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>MacOS on Life Deletion Guide</title><link>https://liguobao.github.io/tags/macos/</link><description>Recent content in MacOS on Life Deletion Guide</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 24 Jun 2025 23:36:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://liguobao.github.io/tags/macos/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>macOS Lossless Migration of PC WeChat Chat Records</title><link>https://liguobao.github.io/p/wechat-backup/</link><pubDate>Tue, 24 Jun 2025 23:36:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://liguobao.github.io/p/wechat-backup/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Migrating chat records on mobile basically uses WeChat&amp;rsquo;s internal tools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cross-machine migration on macOS requires some fiddling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After researching, you actually just need to backup&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;$HOME/Library/Containers/com.tencent.xinWeChat&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The entire folder to the new machine,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Keep WeChat versions consistent on both sides,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Basically nothing else needs to be done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So with GPT&amp;rsquo;s help,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I wrote the following script backup_wechat.sh&lt;/p&gt;
